            "answer_text": "Yes, I've had several friends who never had to pay a dime at a 4 year university after graduating with honors at a 2 year school. Just keep up your grades, go through the school's honors program (try to get invited to join a 2 year school honors society), present at conferences, do community service, be active in clubs, and apply to lots of scholarships. The community college is one of the gems of the US educational system. ",
